fields.value: Research Findings of Comparative Empirical Investigation of 36 OECD and EU Member States

dsDescriptionValue.value: These are research findings of comparative empirical investigation of 36 OECD and EU Member States that were compiled from the criteria and factors of the Comparative Political Data Set (1960-2013) is a collection of political and institutional data which have been assembled in the context of the research projects ‘Die Handlungsspielräume des Nationalstaates’ and ‘Critical junctures: An international comparison’ directed by Klaus Armingeon and funded by the Swiss National Science Foundation. This dataset consists of (mostly) annual data for 36 OECD and EU Member States for the period of 1960 to 2013.  However, the authors analyzed the period of 1990-2013 for 36 OECD and EU Member States. The research findings consist of  (1) Total Variance Explained (Initial Eigenvalues, Extraction Sums of Squared Loadings); (2) Component Matrix; (3) Regression Analysis; (4) Frequencies and Percentages of the OECD and EU Member States; and (5) Frequency Histogram of the OECD and EU Member States (1990-2013).

fields.value: These research findings are a part of an investigation that was written in the framework of a large-scale practical research project that is entitled ‘Chinese Administrative Law and Its Influence on the Commercial Achievement of PRC: Lessons / Recommendations for Turkey (Çin İdare Hukuku ve ÇHC Ticari Başarısına Etkileri: Türkiye İçin Dersler / Öneriler) (Project Grant No: YAPKO – 18-2017/27)’ and conducted at Istanbul Commerce University. Furthermore, these research findings are also a part of a research article that is an updated and extended version of the proceeding that was developed for the 24th International Political Science Association (IPSA) World  Congress of Political Sciences that was held between 23-28 July 2016 at the Poznan Congress Center in Poznan (Poland).
